TEST POWER AND STATION SERVICE PURCHASE AND SALE AGREEMENT TERMS AND CONDITIONS
This Test Power and Station Service Purchase and Sale Agreement (Agreement) dated as of April 6, 2018, between Union Electric Company, d/b/a Ameren Missouri (Ameren) and TG High Prairie, LLC (Project Company) sets forth the terms and conditions pursuant to which: (i) Station Service will be provided to Project Company, and (ii) Ameren will purchase and receive and Project Company will sell and deliver Test Power from the Project Company windfarm to be constructed in Schuyler and Adair Counties Missouri ("Windfarm"). As used throughout this Agreement, Ameren and Project Company may be each referred to as a Party and collectively as the Parties.
1. DEFINITIONS
Adverse System Impact: shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Generator Interconnection Agreement.
Ameren Load Node: means the commercial pricing node established in the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO") energy market for pricing energy delivered from the MISO energy market to the Ameren load.
Build Transfer Agreement: means the Build Transfer Agreement by and between Union Electric Company (d/b/a Ameren Missouri) and TG High Prairie Holdings, LLC dated as of [DATE].
Delivery Point: means the point where the connection facilities of Project Company connect to the transmission owner's 345kV (or such other voltage, if applicable) transmission facilities for purposes of delivering the Test Power generated at the Windfarm to the Ameren load.
Generator Interconnection Agreement: means the Generator Interconnection Agreement to be entered into by and among transmission owner, Project Company, and the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc.
LMP: means locational marginal price as such term is defined in the MISO Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Markets Tariff, as amended from time to time.
Station Service: means the power delivered to the Windfarm for purposes of supplying the Windfarm energy needs when the Windfarm is not generating sufficient energy to self-supply its own needs.
Test Power: means the power generated by the Windfarm and delivered to the transmission system for purposes of commissioning and testing one or more wind turbines prior to the Windfarm being declared commercially operational pursuant to the terms of the Build Transfer Agreement.
2. TERM a. The effective date of this Agreement shall be the date set forth in the preamble above. b. Notwithstanding the effective date of this Agreement, Project Company shall not deliver Test Power to Ameren until the date the following conditions have been satisfied: (i) Project Company's generator interconnection at the Delivery Point is in service; (ii) Project Company has provided written notice to Ameren that Project Company is ready to begin testing the wind turbine(s) at the Windfarm; (iii) Project Company has sought and received such other required approvals for generating Test Power, including but not limited to, approvals from the MISO. Unless terminated earlier pursuant to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, the Term shall end on the closing date pursuant to the Build Transfer Agreement ("Proposed Transaction"), or in the event such transaction does not close, the date the Build Transfer Agreement is terminated.
3. Pre-Closing Date Operation Date Testing All pre-Closing Date operation date testing shall be conducted to commission the wind turbines in accordance with the requirements set forth in the Generator Interconnection Agreement. The Parties shall coordinate with each other and with the MISO prior to Project Company generating any Test Power pursuant to this Agreement. The Parties agree that testing shall not occur during periods when Ameren reasonably determines the proposed testing could cause an Adverse System Impact.
4. PRICING a. Test Power. For each megawatt-hour of Test Power supplied to Ameren by Project Company at the Delivery Point, Ameren shall pay to Project Company an hourly megawatt-hour rate equal to the applicable hourly real- time LMP at the Ameren Load Node for the hour or portion thereof in which such Test Power was supplied. b. Station Service. (i) If Ameren provides Station Service to Project Company through the Delivery Point, such Station Service will be provided pursuant to the Small Primary Service Rate Ameren has on file with the Missouri Public Service Commission (or in the event there is a more appropriate rate at the time Station Service is provided, such other rate). (ii) If Station Service is provided by a third party (e.g. a cooperative), Ameren shall cooperate with the third party to provide meter data and such other information that may be necessary for the third party to bill Project Company for Station Service.
5. PAYMENTS/INVOICES a. Invoices shall be issued by Ameren to Project Company during the month following the calendar month for which either Test Power or Station Service, as applicable, was provided or received hereunder. b. The invoices shall contain sufficient detail and reflect: (i) the amount of Test Power received by Ameren during the previous month and the total amount due and payable by Ameren to Project Company for such Test Power, and (ii) if Station Service is provided by Ameren, the amount of Station Service provided to Project Company during the previous month and total amount due and payable by Project Company to Ameren for such Station Service. c. Each month the total amount due and payable by Ameren to Project Company for Test Power and the total amount due and payable by Project Company to Ameren for any Station Service provided to Project Company (if applicable) will be netted. Such owing Party shall remit payment to the non-owing Party in full no later than 20 calendar days from the date the invoice is delivered to Project Company. d. If the owing Party fails to timely remit all undisputed amounts on the monthly invoice to the non-owing Party as required herein, the non-owing Party may assess a late payment fee of 1.5% per month.
6. TAXES Any applicable license, franchise, gross receipts, occupation or similar charge or tax levied by any taxing authority on the amounts billed pursuant to this Agreement (collectively Taxes) will be so designated and added as a separate item to the monthly invoice.
7. NOTICES a. Any notice, demand or request required or permitted to be given by any Party to the other Party in writing shall be effective when delivered and may be so given, tendered or delivered, by recognized national courier, or by depositing the same with the united States Postal Service with postage prepaid, for delivery by certified or registered mail, addressed to the Party, or personally delivered to the Party, at the address set forth in this Section 7. In addition to the foregoing, written notice also may be delivered electronically to the email address of the contact person set forth in this Section 7 below. Either Party may change the contact information set forth in this Section 7 by giving five (5) business days written notice prior to the effective date of the change.
b. Contacts for Agreement Issues.
Ameren Contact Project Company Contact David Hennen Dan Thompson Ameren Services Company TG High Prairie, LLC 1901 Chouteau Avenue (MC 1310) 11512 El Camino Real St. Louis, MO 63103 San Diego, CA 92130 314-554-3071 847-477-3579 dhennen@ameren.com dthompson@terra-gen.com
c. Contacts for Test Power Coordination.
Ameren Contact Project Company Contact David Meiners Dan Thompson Ameren Services Company TG High Prairie, LLC 1901 Chouteau Avenue (MC 615) 11512 El Camino Real St. Louis, MO 63103 San Diego, CA 92130 314-554-3555 847-477-3579 dmeiners@ameren.com dthompson@terra-gen.com
8. WAIVER Except as otherwise set forth in this Agreement, failure or delay on the part of either Party to exercise any right, power, or privilege under this Agreement shall not operate as a waiver of such right, power or privilege of this Agreement.
9. GOVERNING LAW The validity, interpretation and performance of this Agreement shall be governed by and performed in accordance with the laws of the State of Missouri, and without regard to principles of conflicts of law.
10. MODIFICATIONS TO AGREEMENT The Parties agree that this Agreement may be modified only by written amendment executed by the authorized representatives of both Parties.
11. COUNTERPARTS This Agreement may be executed simultaneously in two or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original, but all of which together shall constitute one and the same instrument.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties to this Agreement have executed and delivered this Agreement on the date and year first set out above.
